text=<<|{{Documentation Index}}|>> [[nogroupfooter]][[nogroupheader]]께Every WikiGroup can have GroupHeader and [=GroupFooter=] pages that contain markup that should be included at the beginning or end of each page within the group.  This feature is primarily used for:께* adding a disclaimer or heading to all of the pages of a group* defining custom WikiStyles that may be used for all pages in a group* replacing the default headers and/or footers for pages in a group (using @@[=[[=]noheader]]@@ and @@[=[[=]nofooter]]@@ -- see SpecialMarkups)께GroupHeaders allow WikiUsers to create groups with custom headers and footers without having to coordinate with a WikiAdministrator.  For even more control, {{WikiAdministrator}}s can do PerGroupCustomizations as a {{LocalCustomization|s}}.께A wiki page within a group can suppress the default GroupHeader or [=GroupFooter=] by using the @@[=[[nogroupheader]]=]@@ and @@[=[[nogroupfooter]]=]@@ markups.께%trail%<<|PmWiki.DocumentationIndex|>>
